Cell.Text: It's an old family. Very well-respected throughout the Reach. | The Silver-Bloods run nearly all the lands in this Hold, as well as the local inn. | And of course, they own Cidhna Mine, the finest prison and source of silver in Skyrim.

Node.Caption: MS01RhiadaSilverBloodsTopic: I want to know about the Silver-Bloods.

Cell.Text: You want Thonar Silver-Blood. He handles all the family business. | If you're here to talk politics, though, you'd want his brother Thongvor. He spends most of his time in Understone Keep.

For one, the Jarl. It goes without saying that he relies heavily on us for our silver and support. | Also all the miners, farmers, and laborers in the Reach get their coin through us. | Nepos the Nose handles the papers there. He has a way with the workers.

Node.Caption: MS01RhiadaPatronsTopic: What kind of patrons do you have?

Cell.Text: I'm afraid he's asked to not be disturbed. He has important business.
[S] Oh, I'm sorry to keep you. Head right in.
No. He isn't.
[S] Riches are a gate-opener around here. Head right in.
Private business, I mean. No visitors.
[S] Go... go right ahead then. Don't let me keep you.
I must have misheard you. Did you say you were leaving?
I doubt he'll be free, but all right.
What are you doing here? I told them no visitors.

[S] G|The Imperial agent? That's right. I knew. How many dogs is the Elder Council going to send after me? | This is my business. My city. You Empire lovers should learn to stay out of it. | Now get out.

Node.Caption: MS01ThonarTopic01: I'm here to talk about Margret.

Cell.Text: [S] G|They're crazy. Think they rule the Reach. | Well guess who really runs things around here? Me. I own the mines. I make the coin pass to the right hands. | That answer your inane questions? Now get out.

Node.Caption: MS01ThonarTopic02: I want answers about the Forsworn.

Cell.Text: [S] G|What did you expect? That no one was going to notice you butting into business that wasn't yours? | The guards know who holds the purse strings in this city, and I don't like snoops. | Markarth is my city. You have no right looking into my business. Now get out.

Node.Caption: MS01ThonarTopic03: Did you send that guard to threaten me?

Cell.Text: My wife. They killed her. | Damn Madanach. Damn his Forsworn backside.
No you're not. You want to know what the Forsworn really are?
Shut up. Only the gods can judge me. You want to know what the Forsworn really are?
Fine. You want to know what the Forsworn really are?
[S] They're my puppets. I have their "king" rotting in Cidhna Mine. | He was supposed to keep them under control.

[S] When their uprising was crushed, I had Madanach brought to me. He was a wild animal, but a useful one. | I offered him a stay from execution if he used his influence to deal with any annoyances that came up. Competitors, agents, idiots. | So I've let him run his little Forsworn rebellion from inside Cidhna Mine. Now he's out of control.

Node.Caption: MS01ThonarDealTopic: You made a deal with the Forsworn?

Cell.Text: [S] G|You already got what you wanted, you damn hound. This is your fault. | You and Madanach are animals, and I'll see you both rot to death in Cidhna Mine for this. | Now get out of my house!

Node.Caption: MS01ThonarMadanachDealTopic: Want me to take care of Madanach?

Cell.Text: G|Get of my house. Now.
Madanach. The King in Rags. | While we were off fighting the Elves in the Great War, Madanach was busy ruling over the Reach. | Until Ulfric came and put them down.
My prison. The source of half the silver in Skyrim. | Madanach and his Forsworn know how to dig, I'll give them that.
